---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import wwComponentsBlueprint from "../images/ww-components-02.jpg";
import wwComponentsPreview from "../images/ww-components-01.jpg";
import numeral from "../svg/numeral-two.svg?raw";
---

<section class="pt-[120px]">
  <div class="max-w-[1752px] mx-auto px-8 flex flex-row items-center">
    <div class="h-[1px] w-[16px] bg-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
    <div
      class="w-[32px] h-[32px] bg-[var(--color-primary)] border-4 border-[var(--color-bg)] outline outline-1 outline-[var(--color-border)] z-10 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--color-bg)]"
    >
      <Fragment set:html={numeral} />
    </div>
    <div class="h-[1px] flex-grow bg-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container px-8 flex flex-row pt-[96px] pb-[120px]">
    <div>
      <h1 class="w-[440px] text-[var(--color-primary)]">WeWeb Components</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-secondary)]">2022 - Present</p>
    </div>
    <div class="w-[560px] text-[var(--color-secondary)]">
      <p>
        Offering basic UI components is essential for any app builder to compete
        with the vast number of libraries available in standard coding
        approaches. However, a common limitation among most app builders is the
        lack of deep customizability.
        <br />
        <br />

        Inspired by the power of Radix and the aesthetics of Shadcn libraries in
        the coding world, we set out to revamp our element toolkit, focusing on
        full customizability, functionality and accessibility.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container grid grid-cols-5 gap-[16px]">
    <div class="col-span-3">
      <Image
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        src={wwComponentsPreview}
        alt=""
        width={1610}
        height={1200}
        quality={"max"}
      />
    </div>
    <div class="col-span-2">
      <Image
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        src={wwComponentsBlueprint}
        alt=""
        width={1152}
        height={1200}
        quality={"max"}
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
